---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'SafetyWing in Netherlands', level: 2 },
  { id: 'dutch-context', text: 'Dutch Insurance Context', level: 2 },
  { id: 'limitations', text: 'Limitations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose SafetyWing', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Netherlands', href: '/countries/netherlands/insurance' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing vs Cigna', href: '/compare/safetywing-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Nomad Insurance', coverage: 'Travel medical', price: '€42-65/mo' },
  { plan: 'Remote Health', coverage: 'Health insurance', price: '€170-230/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing in Netherlands"
  description="Guide to using SafetyWing in the Netherlands. When travel medical insurance works—and when it doesn't."
  headline="SafetyWing in Netherlands"
  subheadline="Travel medical insurance for nomads. Important limitations in the Dutch context."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/netherlands-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a SafetyWing Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/safetywing"
>
  <h2 id="overview">SafetyWing in Netherlands</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing offers affordable travel medical insurance popular with digital nomads. However, the Netherlands' mandatory insurance system creates important considerations for SafetyWing users.
  </p>
  <p>
    SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance—not health insurance. It won't satisfy Dutch mandatory insurance requirements for residents.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">€42/mo</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Starting price</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$250K</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Maximum coverage</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Travel</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Insurance type</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Understanding SafetyWing in NL"
    description="Know the limitations before purchasing."
    buttonText="Learn More"
    buttonHref="/go/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="dutch-context">Dutch Insurance Context</h2>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Critical Consideration</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      If you become a Dutch resident and work in the Netherlands, you're legally required to have Dutch basic health insurance (basisverzekering). SafetyWing Nomad Insurance does not satisfy this requirement. Using only SafetyWing while working in NL may result in fines and forced enrollment in Dutch insurance.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3>When SafetyWing Can Work</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing may be appropriate if you're:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Short-term tourist:</strong> Visiting Netherlands temporarily (under 3 months)</li>
    <li><strong>Transit nomad:</strong> Passing through, not establishing residency</li>
    <li><strong>Student without work:</strong> Some international students may be exempt from Dutch insurance</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>When SafetyWing Won't Work</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Working for a Dutch employer</li>
    <li>Self-employed (ZZP) in Netherlands</li>
    <li>Establishing Dutch residency</li>
    <li>Staying longer than tourist visa allows</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="limitations">Limitations</h2>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">What SafetyWing Doesn't Cover</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
      <li><strong>Pre-existing conditions:</strong> Completely excluded</li>
      <li><strong>Routine care:</strong> Checkups, preventive care not covered</li>
      <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Not covered</li>
      <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> Not covered (except emergency complications)</li>
      <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Ongoing treatment not covered</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Dutch Cost Context</h3>
  <p>
    Netherlands has moderate-to-high healthcare costs:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GP visit:</strong> €30-50 (though typically covered by insurance)</li>
    <li><strong>Specialist:</strong> €100-200</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency room:</strong> €200-500+</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital day:</strong> €500-1,000+</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance vs Remote Health</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Nomad Insurance (€42/mo):</strong> Travel medical only. Not suitable for NL residents.</li>
    <li><strong>Remote Health (€170+/mo):</strong> Actual health insurance. May work for some situations but still may not satisfy Dutch requirements.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose SafetyWing in Netherlands</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Potentially Appropriate</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Short-term tourists</li>
        <li>Digital nomads passing through</li>
        <li>Those not establishing residency</li>
        <li>Supplement to Dutch insurance for travel</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Not Appropriate</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Those working in Netherlands</li>
        <li>Dutch residents</li>
        <li>Self-employed in NL</li>
        <li>Anyone requiring Dutch insurance</li>
        <li>Long-term stays</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>The Bottom Line</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing doesn't replace Dutch mandatory insurance. If you're living and working in the Netherlands, you need Dutch basic insurance—SafetyWing is not a legal alternative. For short-term visitors or those passing through, SafetyWing can provide emergency coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Need Proper Dutch Coverage?"
    description="Compare options for Netherlands residents."
    buttonText="See All Options"
    buttonHref="/go/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Dutch insurance law is strict. If you work in NL or establish residency, you must have Dutch basic insurance. SafetyWing does not satisfy this requirement. Consult with the SVB for your specific situation.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
